brief_title: Diuretics, Hypertension, and Arrhythmias Clinical Trial
brief_summary: To determine whether hypertensive patients with ECG abnormalities and receiving hydrochlorothiazide diuretics were at increased risk of sudden death.
condition: Cardiovascular Diseases Death, Sudden, Cardiac Heart Arrest Heart Diseases Hypertension
eligibility_criteria: Men, ages 35 to 70, with ECG abnormalities, diastolic blood pressure less than 95 mm Hg at entry. Subjects had been treated for at least six months by their own physicians with hydrochlorothiazide (HCT), HCT and potassium supplementation, triamteren
